  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dda\u0dc2\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1: \u0db1\u0dc0 \u0d85\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0db8\u0dda \u0dad\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0d94\u0db6 \u0daf\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0daf?",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Dinesh Gunawardena: Do you know this information about the new Prime Minister?",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Dinesh Gunawardena was sworn in today (July 22) as the new Prime Minister of the new interim government led by President Ranil Wickremesinghe.",
        "He was sworn in before President Ranil Wickremesinghe at the Prime Minister's office in Malpara, Colombo.",
        "The three armed forces chiefs and other members of parliament also participated in this event.",
        "Also, a spokesperson of the President's office said that the new cabinet will also be sworn in today at around 12.30 pm.",
        "Abhinava Agramatya Dinesh Gunawardena's parents are Phillip Gunawardena, nicknamed Boralugoda Sinhaya, the father of socialism in this country, and Kusuma Gunawardena, known as Rathu Kusuma of the Left.",
        "Born on March 2, 1949, Dinesh Gunawardena has been the leader of the People's United Front since 1973, after the death of Philip Gunawardena.",
        "Dinesh Gunawardena received his schooling from the Royal College, Colombo. Later, he earned associate degrees in business administration, management, and business administration, management and international transportation from the Netherlands Business University and the University of Oregon.",
        "She died suddenly in the mid-1980s and his two children are Yadamini Gunawardena and Sankhapali Gunawardena, a current Member of Parliament.",
        "Indika Gunawardena who was a minister, Githanjana Gunawardena who held the post of Deputy Speaker as well as Deputy Minister twice, Prasanna Gunawardena who was the mayor of Colombo and writer Lakmali Gunawardena are his brothers and sisters.",
        "Dinesh Gunawardena, the leader of the People's United Front, was the candidate for Avissawella in the 1977 parliamentary elections, but failed to get elected. But in the by-election of 1983, he was the Maharagama candidate of the People's United Front and entered the Parliament for the first time with a historic victory in that election.",
        "Since then, he represented the Parliament from time to time, failed to win in the general election held in 1994, won again in the election held in the year 2000 from the Colombo district and held many senior ministerial posts in many governments."
      ],
